Test1 04/08/2025

1) New OS Build with LVM
/dev/sda			50Gb
/dev/rootvg/rootlv		20Gb
/boot				1Gb
/dev/rootvg/varlv		5Gb
/dev/rootvg/tmplv		3Gb
/dev/rootvg/optlv		5Gb
swap				1Gb
/dev/rootvg/homelv		2Gb
Servername: ll3369srv, IP: 192.168.29/1.180

2) create users asadmin, was, oracle, web and grid users, primary groups also same as usernames and then modify attributes as per the below values.
Home directory: /export/app/home; Shell: /bin/sh; Secondary Groups: unix, backup and dba; oracle & grid umask value should be 0002.

3) Configure /publicdata file system with 10Gb (/dev/sdb) and migrate to 20Gb 

4) Configure below file systems with sdc-10Gb Webvg, sdd-20Gb javavg, sde-5Gb oraclevg, sdf-5Gb sybasevg, sdg-2Gb salesvg.

5) Export below file systems on nfsclient
/webdata1	hardmount to nfsclient
/webdata2	hardmount to nfsclient
/javadata1	softdirect to *
/javadata2	softdirect to *
/oracle		softindirect to 192.168.29.0/24	/database
/sybase		softindirect to 192.168.29.0/24	/database
/salesforce	softindirect to 192.168.29.0/24	/database

6) modify all shared file systems to respective owners on nfsclient server
drwxr-xr-x 2 web web  1024 Aug  1 20:14 /webdata1
drwxr-xr-x 2 web web  1024 Aug  1 20:14 /webdata2
drwxr-xr-x 2 asadmin asadmin  1024 Aug  1 20:14 /javadata1
drwxr-xr-x 2 asadmin asadmin  1024 Aug  1 20:14 /javadata2
drwxr-xr-x 2 oracle oracle  1024 Aug  1 20:14 /oracle
drwxr-xr-x 2 was was  1024 Aug  1 20:14 /sybase
drwxr-xr-x 2 grid grid  1024 Aug  1 20:14 /salesforce

7) oracle, was, grid users need to run all service, disk & packages related commands. web & asadmin should be run all unix commands. All these configurations need to setup with individual sudo files

8) /webdata (XFS) file system creation with 10Gb /dev/sdh1(5Gb), /dev/sdi1(5Gb) and extented to 20Gb /dev/sdj1 & /dev/sdh1
